The paper proposes a multi-task learning framework for biomedical named entity recognition (BioNER) based on neural network models. The paper focuses on the application of deep learning techniques to improve BioNER, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of character- and word-level information, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the application of text-mining approaches to help biomedical scientists better exploit knowledge in biomedical literature, which could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
